ciscoNmsApplHealthMIB.name: ciscoNmsApplHealthMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoNmsApplHealthMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-nmsapplhealth@cisco.com
ciscoNmsApplHealthMIB.description: This MIB defines Cisco NMS Application (cna) Health Status Notifications and the related objects. These notifications will be sent to the OSS/NMS to inform them about the NMS application status (started, stopped, failed, busy etc.) or any abnormal exit of applications.

cnaHealthNotifSeqNum.name: cnaHealthNotifSeqNum
cnaHealthNotifSeqNum.description: The value of this object indicates the sequence number of notifications in order for the NMS/OSS to detect missing notification(s).

cnaHealthTable.name: cnaHealthTable
cnaHealthTable.description: A table of information about the health of one or more Cisco NMS application(s).

cnaHealthTableEntry.name: cnaHealthTableEntry
cnaHealthTableEntry.description: Entries appear in this table for each possible alarm state.

cnaHealthTableIndex.name: cnaHealthTableIndex
cnaHealthTableIndex.description: This acts as the index to the cnaHealthTable.

cnaHealthStatusChangeTime.name: cnaHealthStatusChangeTime
cnaHealthStatusChangeTime.description: The time when a change in the health status of Cisco NMS Application occurs.

cnaHealthName.name: cnaHealthName
cnaHealthName.description: The value of this object indicates the name of the NMS application, the notification is about.

cnaHealthStatus.name: cnaHealthStatus
cnaHealthStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the health/status of the NMS application, the notification is reporting about. The possible values are: started(1) : started & initialized successfully stopped(2) : stopped successfully busy(3) : not able to respond to any request from health monitor until the status changed to started failed(4) : upon detecting error condition, logged and exited exited(5) : abnormally exited without logging

cnaHealthSevLevel.name: cnaHealthSevLevel
cnaHealthSevLevel.description: Indicates the severity level of the cna health status Notifications.

cnaHealthComLineArgs.name: cnaHealthComLineArgs
cnaHealthComLineArgs.description: The value of this object indicates the command-line arguments of the NMS application being reported about in the notifications.

cnaHealthStatusDesc.name: cnaHealthStatusDesc
cnaHealthStatusDesc.description: The value of this object gives a detailed description of the health/ status of the application being reported in a notification. In case of failed(4) status, this field must indicate the error description. For any other cnaStatus, this field may contain a description to qualify the cnaStatus, like 'Started & initialized succesfully' or an empty string.

cnaHealthNotif.name: cnaHealthNotif
cnaHealthNotif.description: This notification is sent out to notify normal startup, shutdown, intermediate health/status (ex: busy etc.), failed or exit status.

cnaHealthMIBCompliance.name: cnaHealthMIBCompliance
cnaHealthMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco NMS Application Health Monitor MIB.

cnaHealthMIBGroup.name: cnaHealthMIBGroup
cnaHealthMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Cisco NMS Application normal health info

cnaHealthNotifGroup.name: cnaHealthNotifGroup
cnaHealthNotifGroup.description: The set of notification events a Cisco NMS application supports.
